descript.abstract: Brown County Data Source: This product is a compilation of cadastral data from many sources. These sources include, but are not limited to, U.S. General Land Office survey notes, deeds, plats, survey maps, easements, survey notes from land surveyors, town road records and right-of-way plats. The maps are different scales and were made on dates ranging from the early 1800's to the present. Deeds and other written documentation date from the early 1800's to the present. Deeds and other records date from the early 1800's to the present. Survey practices were used to construct the frame work and are followed where interpretation of information was required. This product is intended to provide a representation of the shape and location of tax parcels and is suitable for the intended use. Roads file was created from an extraction of the Brown County tax parcel maps 10CL AutoCad drawing layer.
descript.purpose: The street centerline file was created to aid government agencies geocode local address files. Users include Brown County 911 dispatch.

attracc.attraccr: All data has been reviewed for correct application of attributes are accurate and true to the best of Brown County's knowledge. Attribute information was obtained from Brown County AS400 land records, parcel drawing 26ADD layer and field verification.

dataqual.logic: All road centerline geographical entities are obtained from the Brown County Survey Department tax parcel drawings 10CL AutoCad drawing layer. The Brown County Planning Department converted this layer to an ArcInfo road centerline file and added attribute information. In September 2002, the Brown County Land Information Office converted the ESRI Arc/INFO Coverage to an ArcSDE Geodatabase which is now the "master" centerline data.
dataqual.complete: Road centerline file has been completed throughout Brown County and is maintained as needed.

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal accuracy is based on the monuments of the US Public Land Survey System, geodetic control stations and local survey control positions tied into those systems. Where required, additional survey points were located to control the locations of parcel and right of way lines. Road centerline is an approximate centerline of the AutoCad drawing ROW layer (10Road). Where ROW is a divided road multiple centerlines were heads up digitized on 1992 orthophotos 1 meter pixel accuracy.

procstep.procdesc: Deeds, land survey maps and other related documents are read. Locations of line work is determined and the parcels are mapped. Parcel identification numbers and originating document numbers are obtained from the Brown County Land Records System. Where records are too ambiguous key points are located in the field using GPS and conventional surveying techniques. Title ambiguities are discussed with the County Surveyor/Property Lister, Property Listing Manager and Property Analysts to correct problems. The mapping is done by municipal taxing districts. The parcel maps are updated as the Property Listing division processes information. Subsequently, the Planning Department then imports the 10CL data into the existing road centerline and corresponding attributes are added.

attr.attrdef: Code to depict permitted direction of travel. This field was set up for the ArcView 3.x Network Analyst extension. Allowable values: FT, FT, or N; where FT=Travel is permitted from the start to the end of the line only, which is the same as the digitized direction; TF=travel is permitted from the end of the line to the start of the line only, which is the opposite of the digitized direction of the vector.. N=Travel is permitted in neither direction; the line is closed to travel. Any other values or no data in this field will indicate that travel is permitted in both directions
